The Niger Police Command yesterday released N64 million to 30 families of policemen who died in active service between 2020 and 2021. Spokesman of the Command Wasiu Abiodun said in a statement yesterday that Commissioner of Police Monday Bala Kuryas released the money on behalf of the Inspector-General of Police, Alkali Baba Usman. “This welfare gesture is an initiative of the IGP Group Life Assurance geared towards improving the lives and capacity of the families left behind by these heroic officers who lost their lives in the line of duty,'” he said.   Customs seizes N755m cars, consumables in Niger     Boko Haram abducts travellers on Maiduguri road     EFCC arrests 19 suspected Yahoo boys in Kogi   While presenting the cheques to the next of kin of the fallen operatives, the commissioner appreciated the Inspector-General of Police for such laudable initiative. He encouraged the beneficiaries to judiciously use the cash for the welfare of the families. The families expressed satisfaction for the gesture. “We will ensure that the resources will be well managed towards an improved standard of our living,” the statement quoted the beneficiaries as saying.